{
  "stem": "9987.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But during the night that he was standing there, he got the pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He got pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my brother Joshua and I didn't feel that we can handle a sick brother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The-- the borders were already closed between Soviet side and Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But smugglers were going back, back and forth.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So we went, we hired a smuggler, and we smuggled my younger brother back home to Krosno, to recover.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] All of a sudden a couple weeks later, or two, three weeks later, we found out that the Soviets don't want us there either, that everybody has to take an internal passport [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] or you become a Soviet citizen or you go back to Germany or you become a refugee.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Now we didn't want either.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We didn't want to become Soviet citizen, because we didn't know how long it's going to last.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my older brother Joshua and I, with another group of young people from our town, we hired the same smuggler and we smuggled ourselves back to the German side.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So in January 1940, we crossed the river San.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was all frozen, ice and snow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We crossed it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They loaded us out into a hiding house all ready on the German side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the next day, we-- we-- they provided a horse and buggy, and we came back to Krosno.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we came back to Krosno in January 1940, we saw the mistake that we did.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was the biggest mistake to go back to the German side.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we tried to make up our mind, we tried to convince our parents and the whole family to smuggle back to the Soviet side.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No matter how bad it is, no use to stay in the German side, because it became terrible.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
